# Cursor Project Rules

## AI Assistant Guidelines
- AI should follow the project structure defined in backend_structure_document.mdc
- When generating code, follow the tech stack defined in tech_stack_document.mdc
- Frontend components must adhere to guidelines in frontend_guidelines_document.mdc
- Follow the app flow outlined in app_flow_document.mdc
- New features should be implemented according to the implementation_plan.mdc

## Code Generation Rules
- Generate complete, working code that can be run immediately
- Include all necessary imports and dependencies
- Follow established patterns in the existing codebase
- Include proper error handling and validation
- Write clean, maintainable code with appropriate comments
- Use TypeScript types for all functions and components

## Documentation Requirements
- Document all API endpoints with parameters and responses
- Include JSDoc comments for all functions and components
- Add comprehensive README files for each major directory
- Comment complex logic and algorithms
- Include usage examples for reusable components

## Testing Expectations
- Write unit tests for all business logic
- Include component tests for UI elements
- Test both success and error scenarios
- Mock external dependencies for reliable testing
- Maintain test coverage above 80% 